SET IS AN UNORDERED COLLECTION OF ELEMENTS WITHOUT DUPLICATE VALUES

>PROBLEM: 
TASK IS TO FIND AVERAGE OF DISTINCT VALUES

>SOLUTION:

def average(array):
    array = set(array)
    AVG = sum(array) / len(array)
    return AVG  

if __name__ == '__main__':
    n = int(input())
    arr = list(map(int, input().split()))
    result = average(arr)
    print(result)
